what are the early warning signs of a stroke sudden numbness or weakness of the face arm or leg especially on one side of the body sudden confusion trouble speaking or understanding sudden trouble seeing in one or both eyes sudden trouble walking dizziness loss of balance or coordination sudden severe headache with no known cause ask the person to smile is it symetrical both sides the same have them close their eyes and put their arms out straight in front of them are they even or does one drift higher or lower ask them some simple questions related to time do they know where they are what year it is who the president is do their answers make sense is there speech clear or slurred have them stick out their tongue does it come straight out or drift to one side check out american stroke association also when in doubt get it checked out by a professional and the sooner the better getting help for a stroke is time sensitive the window of opportunity for certain types of stroke is only hours from onset of symptoms Traumatic brain injury Glossary of medical terms related to communications disorders Apoplexy Multiple sclerosis 3-quinuclidinyl benzilate Autism Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Aerial (dance move) Aphasia First aid Professional wrestling throws Seizure Dyslexia Decompression sickness Equine conformation Hyperthermia Chlorpromazine Dialysis Hormone replacement therapy (trans) Chronic fatigue syndrome Cephalic disorder Diabetic retinopathy Hypoglycemia Breaststroke Milton H. Erickson Professional wrestling holds Diabetes mellitus Butterfly stroke Cancer Stuttering Hearing impairment Psychosis Skateboarding trick Myocardial infarction Migraine Poker jargon Dehydration Epilepsy George Brown, Baron George-Brown Strap-on dildo Myasthenia gravis Syringomyelia Backstroke Snooker M__ni__re___s disease Front crawl Menstrual cycle Concussion of the brain Social rule Humphrey Bogart Boxing Panic attack Swimming Prostate cancer Scientology beliefs and practices Aspartame Stomach ca